--- #slide-ids

# Slide IDs

This slide is addressable as `#slide-ids` — try appending it to the URL.

IDs survive slide reordering, unlike numeric anchors that shift when you insert content above.

Syntax: put `--- #some-id` on the separator **above** the slide you want to name.

--- #pauses

# Progressive Reveal

Pauses split the slide into click-advanced sections.

<!-- pause -->

- First bullet appears on initial render.
<!-- pause -->
- Second bullet appears on next click.
<!-- pause -->
- Third bullet appears after that.

<!-- note: Press right arrow or space to advance through pauses. -->

--- #variants

# Variants

The standard version of the slide.

---variant: punchy
# Variants — Punchy

A shorter, more aggressive version of the same slide. Agents can propose alternatives without overwriting your work.

---variant: data-heavy
# Variants — Data-Heavy

A version backed by numbers. Toggle variants in the presenter UI or pick one at export with `--variant`.

--- #comments

# Comments & Notes

Content that stays in the file but off the rendered slide.

<!-- note: Speaker notes show in presenter mode — for what you say out loud. -->
<!-- ai: AI notes carry agent context — rationale, constraints, instructions for the next session. -->
